On the nature of spam in comment sections, I believe we are typically unfair in the depiction of those who perpetrate it as "mindless", and other such things, accusations which, upon more careful consideration, can not but be untrue. To cooperate with others with no seeming goal but humouring oneself or keeping a pattern perceived to be satisfying is in no way mindless, nor is it "following the hivemind". There is nothing compelling the willing participants into spamming as is usually the case in other demonstations of hive-like thought. They gain no reddit upvotes; this site thankfully has no such system. To cooperate for individual benefit is simply exercising logical action, and is a hallmark for the survival of the human species. Therefore do I dismiss accusations of comment chains being reliant on the convention of the mindless. Of course, expressions of annoyance are not unjustified, either.
